Description: Part of the shoulder and rim of a tall jar: of light brown pottery, with a red slip on the exterior and black in the centre of the section. The outer surface bears an incised inscription of two signs. Good condition.
Curator's comments: Compare E. Amélineau, ‘Les Nouvelles Fouilles d’Abydos’ I, (1895-6), pls. XVII; A. Scharff, ‘Die Altertümer der Vor – und Frühzeit Ägyptens I (Berlin, 1929-31), no. 381 and abb. 67; W. M. F. Petrie, 'Tarkhan' II (London, 1914), pl. XX, II; W. B. Emery, ‘Excavations at Saqqara : the tomb of Hemaka' (Cairo, 1938), pl. 40; W. B. Emery, 'Great tombs of the First Dynasty; excavations at Sakkara' I' (Cairo, 1949), 155, fig. 90, no. 29; W. B. Emery, 'Great tombs of the First Dynasty; excavations at Sakkara' III (London, 1958), pl. 76, nos. 10-13. Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl.XLIX, 450.
